place.name: NORTH BARSHAM
place.gazetteerText: BARSHAM (North), a parish in Walsingham district, Norfolk; adjacent to the Norfolk railway, 2 miles SW of New Walsingham. Post Town, New Walsingham under Fakenham. Acres, 1,015. Real property, £1,609. Pop., 57. Houses, 14. The property is divided among few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich Value, £244.* Patron, the Earl of Orford. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
